Thomas Hartleb, News24(File: News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A man was shot dead while fleeing from police near Somerset Mall, Cape Town, on Saturday morning.Police began pursuing a silver VW Polo with four occupants they noticed speeding from Garden Village towards Somerset Mall around 06:30, Western Cape police spokesperson Colonel Tembinkosi Kinana said in a statement.Two men, one of them armed, jumped from the moving car near the mall. A shoot-out with police followed, during which one man was shot dead and another arrested. The other two were still at large.&nbsp;&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.